at a later date, involving a greater or lesser degree of disability.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
4.2.3 The insurance sum payable amounts to DKK 750,000 in the case of
complete disability (100%). The compensation payable amounts to the
percentage of the maximum insurance sum that corresponds to the
established degree of disability.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
The degree of disability shall be determined in accordance with the
disability table that the National Board of Industrial Injuries in Denmark
applies at the time of the injury. If the degree of disability cannot be
directly established using the disability table applied by the National
Board of Industrial Injuries in Denmark, the injured party's degree of
medical disability shall be determined using principles corresponding to
those on which the disability table is based, according to the level of
physical functional impairment.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
In all cases, the degree of disability will be established on a purely
medical basis, irrespective of any reduction in earning capacity, the
particular profession of the injured party or other individual
conditions. Loss of earning capacity is not covered.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
4.2.4 The degree of disability cannot exceed 100%.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
4.2.5 An existing disability cannot result in the compensation payable
being set higher than if no such disability had existed.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
4.2.6 Up to DKK 10,000 is payable in compensation for treatment of
acute dental damage arising during the period of travel as a result
of an accident. The dental treatment must have commenced abroad, but
may, if necessary, be completed once the injured party has returned
to his/her country of residence.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
4.2.7 In the event of death, payment is made to the closest
relative(s). In this context, 'the closest relative(s)' is taken to
mean the insured's spouse or, if the insured is not married, his/her
life partner with whom he/she has shared an address for at least six
.kp on
