4.3.5 Write-down of the value of the item (wear and age).
.br
All items are to be written down according to the following table:
.sp 3mm
Year 1 = no coverage
.br
Year 2 = no coverage (although 85% of the repurchase value for insured
persons resident on Greenland or the Faeroe Islands)
.br
Year 3 = 75% of the repurchase value
.br
Year 4 = 65% of the repurchase value
.br
Year 5 = 50% of the repurchase value
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED
4.4 Double insurance
:SKRSLUT.
.br
If the items covered by the present insurance are also covered by other
insurance policies that exclude double insurance, a reservation of this
kind applies to both insurance policies. In such cases, liability is
divided between the policies in accordance with the provisions in the two
or more policies. However, the insured will never be entitled to higher
compensation from two insurance companies together than the insured could
have obtained had he/she been insured by a single insurance company.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
If the compensation sum payable exceeds the insurance sum in the
individual policy but is within the total insurance sum for the
policies, the compensation obligation is to be shared between the
insurance companies in relation to the respective insurance sums.
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS10.
:FED.
5.0 Force majeure
.br
:SKRSLUT.
:SWISS8.
Insurance coverage does not apply to losses that may arise if
investigation of a claim, repairs or payment of compensation is
delayed on account of war, war-like conditions, civil war, revolution
or revolt, or as a result of intervention from the authorities,
strike, lockout, blockade or similar.
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS10.
:FED.
6.0 Danish Insurance Contracts Act
.br
:SKRSLUT.
:SWISS8.
Insurance policies are otherwise subject to the provisions of the
Danish Insurance Contracts Act to the extent that this has not been
waived in the terms and conditions. Over and above the terms and
conditions mentioned in the present group insurance agreement, the
insurance is subject to Danish law.
